race.comment: DAZZLING LIZZIE (4) was quickly into stride and raced on speed before sticking on for a minor placing second (16.71) at Q Straight in Grade 6. Missed the placings only try here. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Must come into calculations. JEAN'S THING (3) proved too good on debut over 352m at this track to score by 2.75 lengths (20.09). Harder here but expected to feature again. REVA TWIST (2) has been mixing form lately, hitting the frame two back before finishing fourth (20.27) at this track in a Grade 6. Can improve sharply here. GO BLANCHETT GO (1) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.
